{"id":"int-8cb884e0","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T22:54:25.540396Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47.5","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Added timed() helper and wrapped all 5 VLC teardown call sites (retirePlayer stop/media=nil/delegate=nil/new player, play() teardown, pause() stop, stop() stop+media=nil, reduced-buffer giveup stop+media=nil). Also added entry/exit logs in the utility-queue dispose block. Build 141 succeeded; all 52 unit tests pass."}}
{"id":"int-faa322e3","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T22:54:26.458999Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47.6","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"in_progress","old_value":"open"}}
{"id":"int-5ad383da","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T22:55:20.277409Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47.6","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Swapped order in retirePlayer to detach media (and clear delegate) BEFORE calling stop(). Rationale documented in the inline comment: stop() synchronously drains VLC's input/decoder threads, so clearing media first severs the input source and gives stop() nothing to wait on. Build 141 succeeded; all 52 unit tests pass."}}
{"id":"int-9f5fa6ee","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T22:55:21.096835Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47.7","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"in_progress","old_value":"open"}}
{"id":"int-ce4485b1","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T22:57:30.204623Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47.7","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Audit complete. NO orphan VLCMediaPlayer reference found in app code:\n\n1. retirePlayer's [old] capture is the only explicit player capture; dispatched to utility queue.\n2. All DispatchWorkItem closures (interruptionFallbackWorkItem line 320, channelNameOverlayWorkItem line 632, debounce workItem line 651) use [weak self].\n3. The two interruption.ended asyncAfter closures (lines 371, 408) strong-capture self but access self.mediaPlayer (re-evaluated per call) — so they reach the NEW player after a retirePlayer, not the OLD one.\n4. Combine sinks (sxmCancellable line 179, espnCancellable line 190) use [weak self].\n5. VLC delegate methods are 'nonisolated' wrappers that dispatch Task { @MainActor in } — no aNotification capture, and self is either weakly captured or accessed via self.mediaPlayer.\n6. NotificationCenter observers all target AVAudioSession.sharedInstance(), not the media player.\n\nConclusion: the orphan reference responsible for the dealloc-on-main in the FRONTBOARD crash most likely lives inside VLCKit's own dispatch internals (VLCKit posts state-change notifications via NSNotification with the player as object; the runloop's pending notification queue can strong-retain the player). That's outside our control.\n\nThe right mitigation is v47.6 (detach media before stop, done) + v47.8 (bound the network read so poll() can't hang regardless of who runs the final dealloc)."}}
{"id":"int-9724f431","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T22:57:31.113855Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47.8","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"in_progress","old_value":"open"}}
{"id":"int-4f21e9b7","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:00:19.282972Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47.8","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Added --ipv4-timeout=2000 and --ipv6-timeout=2000 to both retirePlayer call sites (startStream and the buffered-playback path).\n\nResearch findings (recorded inline in startStream): VLC's steady-state poll() inside vlc_tls_Read uses an infinite timeout that cannot be configured via libvlc options. The connect timeouts only bound the initial TCP handshake (defaults to 5s, now 2s). For mid-stream stalls — the actual crash mechanism — the syncState() data-flow watchdog (dataFlowStaleTimeout = 8s, line 75) is the only mechanism, and it already exists.\n\nSo v47.8 ships a narrow improvement (faster reconnect on connection-time stalls) and documents the unfixable steady-state case. The combined v47 fix surface is:\n- v47.5: timing instrumentation on all 8 VLC teardown call sites\n- v47.6: detach media before stop in retirePlayer (input severed before drain)\n- v47.7: closure capture audit complete — orphan reference lives inside VLCKit\n- v47.8: 2s connect timeouts + documented limit\n\nBuild 141 succeeded; 52 unit tests pass."}}
{"id":"int-9968ee0d","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:00:49.071895Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47.6","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Swapped order in retirePlayer to detach media (and clear delegate) BEFORE calling stop(). stop() synchronously drains VLC's input/decoder threads, so clearing media first severs the input source. Build 141; 52 tests pass."}}
{"id":"int-932e2a38","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:00:50.046872Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-v47","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"All 4 children closed. Build 141 ships: VLC teardown timing instrumentation, media detached before stop in retirePlayer, 2s TCP connect timeouts, closure capture audit complete. Real-world validation pending: next phone call during CarPlay playback."}}
