{"id":"int-f3649f2b","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:06:34.872846Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-651.3","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Added payload logging at all three NowPlaying surfaces:\n1. updateNowPlayingInfo: each write to MPNowPlayingInfoCenter now logs source (which branch chose the title — sxm/espn/streamMetadata/epg/channelNameOverlay/fallback-loading/fallback-channel), title, artist, album, isLive, state name, rate, hasArtwork.\n2. clearNowPlayingInfo: logs when nowPlayingInfo is wiped.\n3. CarPlayTemplateManager.pushNowPlaying: extended all three log paths (already-on-top, popping back, pushing new) with nowPlayingContext() — current channel name and a live snapshot of MPNowPlayingInfoCenter title/artist/hasArtwork at push time.\n\nBuild 142; 52 tests pass."}}
{"id":"int-36b1c3cf","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:08:49.398971Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-651.1","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"in_progress","old_value":"open"}}
{"id":"int-3c072332","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:09:47.957694Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-651.1","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Two defensive changes shipped (root cause still requires 651.3 logs from a real-world cold-launch session):\n\n1. CarPlayTemplateManager.playChannelAndShowNowPlaying now schedules refreshes at t+1s, +3s, and +5s (was just +1s). Each attempt logs a CarPlay-category line so we can see in the next incident log whether the late refreshes actually find new SXM metadata.\n\n2. AudioPlayerService.refreshNowPlayingInfo now clears ALL change-detection caches (was just lastNowPlayingArtwork). This forces every refresh call to write to MPNowPlayingInfoCenter regardless of whether the values appear unchanged — some CarPlay head units only pick up metadata on a fresh write.\n\nBuild 142; 52 tests pass. The 651.3 instrumentation is what will tell us the actual root cause next time the cold-launch path runs (whether updateNowPlayingInfo fires, what payload it pushes, and whether refresh attempts at 1/3/5s see different data)."}}
{"id":"int-e24467c4","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:09:48.783253Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-651.2","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"in_progress","old_value":"open"}}
{"id":"int-9d639e87","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:12:06.048239Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-651.2","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Added AudioPlayerService.prewarmRemoteCommands() and call it from CarPlaySceneDelegate.didConnect.\n\nWhat it does:\n1. Logs current audio session category/mode/route, current MPNowPlayingInfoCenter state, and playbackState at CarPlay connect — so the next incident log shows what iOS thinks of us before user action.\n2. If nowPlayingInfo is nil, writes a placeholder (rate=0, isLiveStream=true) and sets playbackState=.stopped. The placeholder declares us as a now-playing candidate so iOS routes MPRemoteCommandCenter events to us BEFORE the user picks a channel. Doesn't stomp an active playback session (guards on existingInfo == nil).\n3. Re-asserts session.setActive(true) so any stale post-interruption state is cleared.\n\nBuild 142; 52 tests pass. Hypothesis confirmation pending real-world data: if the 4-minute REMOTE silence repeats with prewarmRemoteCommands logging in place, we'll see whether the session was active, whether anyone else had nowPlayingInfo, and whether our placeholder write succeeded."}}
{"id":"int-09a321f7","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-05-20T23:12:18.165513Z","actor":"Curt LeCaptain","issue_id":"beads_mobilemusic-651.1","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Defensive measures shipped (root cause needs real-world data): (1) CarPlayTemplateManager schedules NowPlaying refreshes at t+1s/+3s/+5s with logged attempts. (2) refreshNowPlayingInfo clears ALL change-detection caches to force a fresh write. Build 142; 52 tests pass."}}
